      "@type": "Project",
      "schema:legalName": "The Celtic Sea Herring Acoustic Survey (CSHAS)",
      "schema:name": "The Celtic Sea Herring Acoustic Survey (CSHAS)",
      "schema:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10793/1732",
      "schema:description": "The Celtic Sea herring acoustic survey (CSHAS) has been undertaken annually in various forms since 1989. Since 2004 the survey has been fixed in October and carried out onboard the RV Celtic Explorer. The survey targets pre-spawning aggregations of herring as they migrate inshore to spawn.  The stock is composed of both autumn and winter spawning components with the latter dominating. Overall, the protracted spawning period of the two components extends from October through to February, with annual variation of up to 3 weeks. Spawning occurs in successive waves in a number of well-known locations including large scale grounds and small discreet spawning beds.\r\nSurvey design and geographical coverage have been modified over the time series to adapt to changes in stock size and behaviour. Since 2016, the wider core distribution area has been surveyed by means of two independent surveys and supplemented with small high resolution adaptive surveys focusing on areas of high abundance.  As well as reporting age stratified relative biomass and abundance of herring in the Celtic Sea, the survey reports time series estimates for relative biomass and abundance for other important small pelagic fish (SPF) species including sprat, anchovy and sardine.\r\nThe survey collects abundance and distribution data on apex predators including marine mammals, tuna species and seabirds. The survey collects hydrographic data and conducts zooplankton sampling over the course of the 21 days at sea.",
